</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Custard Ice Cream</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups heavy cream</li>
            <li>1 cup whole milk</li>
            <li>4 large egg yolks</li>
            <li>3/4 cup granulated sugar</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
            <li>Pinch of salt</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>ice cream</li>
            <li>desert</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a saucepan, heat the heavy cream and whole milk over medium heat until it just begins to simmer. Remove from heat.</li>
            <li>In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg yolks and granulated sugar until well combined.</li>
            <li>Slowly pour the warm milk mixture into the egg yolk mixture, whisking constantly to temper the eggs.</li>
            <li>Return the mixture to the saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens and coats the back of a spoon.</li>
            <li>Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. Allow the custard to cool to room temperature.</li>
            <li>Transfer the custard to an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer's instructions.</li>
            <li>Once churned, transfer the custard ice cream to a lidded container and freeze for at least 4 hours or until firm.</li>
            <li>Scoop and enjoy the rich and velvety Custard Ice Cream!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
